column10:
The game is good like all the other TEKKENs. The only things I dislike are the following:
- No team battle mode;
- No survival mode;
- Arcade mode is way too short;
- Akuma (as a character and for the fact that he is part of the TEKKEN franchise somehow);
- No different storyline like in the other games; there is only 1 story mode + some "episodes" for the minor characters;
- Rage art.

What I liked:
* the first [i]Tekken[/i] on PC and the gameplay was good;
* the game ran smoothly, there were no technical errors and the graphics were good enough;
* in online game mode, everyone else is almost always a million times better than you (keeps you focused and encourages to practice).

What I didn't like:
* the story mode competes in the heavyweight of telenovelas;
* soundtrack;
* for some cool characters and stages you have to pay to unlock them;
* in online game mode, everyone else is almost always a million times better than you (it can get annoying if there are no equal opponents to be found for a longer time period);
* your fingers must be made of iron or rubber or some other durable material if you want to play at a good level for more than half an hour (I played both with a contoller and a joystick, and though joystick clearly has advantages, it can still make your fingers numb).


All in all, great entertainment for a few evenings (or a few years for some people).
